        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 12 at 1:26PM EDT by NWS Tampa Bay Ruskin FL</headline>
        <description>At 126 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Wauchula, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ona, Zolfo Springs, Wauchula, Limestone, Gardner, Crewsville,
Sweetwater, and Bowling Green.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
